==English==
===Etymology===
From Middle French ''[[magasin]]'' ("warehouse", "store") < Italian ''[[magazzino]]'' ("storehouse") < Arabic {{ARchar|[[مخازن]]}} ({{IPAchar|''maχáːzin''}}, "storerooms", "storehouses"), plural of {{ARchar|[[مخزن]]}} (''máχzan'', "storeroom", "storehouse") < {{ARchar|[[خزن]]}} (''χázana'', "to store", "to stock", "to lay up").

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/mæɡəˈzi:n/}}
*{{SAMPA|/%m{g@"zin/}}

====Hyphenation====
mag·a·zine

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[ammunition]] storehouse.
# Detachable ammunition holder enabling multiple [[round]]s of ammunition to be fed to a [[gun]].
# A periodical publication, generally consisting of sheets of paper folded in half and stapled at fold.

